{{Infobox play | name = In a Forest, Dark and Deep | image = | image_size = | caption = | writer = [[Neil LaBute]] | chorus = | characters = | mute = | setting = | premiere = {{Start date|2011|3|14|df=y}} | place = [[Vaudeville Theatre]], London | orig_lang = English | series = | subject = | genre = [[Dark Comedy]] | web = }}
'''''In a Forest, Dark and Deep''''' is a play by [[Neil LaBute]]. It received its world premiere production in the [[West End theatre|West End's]] [[Vaudeville Theatre]] on 14 March 2011 following previews from 3 March 2011, running for a limited season until 4 June 2011. The production starred [[Matthew Fox (actor)|Matthew Fox]] and [[Olivia Williams]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Billington|first=Michael|authorlink=Michael Billington (critic)|title=In a Forest Dark and Deep - review|url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2011/mar/15/in-a-forest-dark-and-deep-review|accessdate=29 November 2013|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=15 March 2011}}</ref>
The play had its American premiere at [[Profiles Theatre Chicago|Profiles Theatre]] in Chicago, Illinois in April 2012 through 3 June.<ref>{{cite news|last=Chicago Tribune|title=Chicago Tribune|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2012-01-17/entertainment/chi-profiles-snags-us-premiere-of-london-hit-announces-plans-for-additional-space-20120117_1_snags-neil-labute-profiles-theatre/|accessdate= 4 April 2012|date=17 January 2012}}</ref> The production stars Darrell W. Cox and Natasha Lowe and was directed by Joe Jahraus.<ref>{{cite web|last=Profiles Theatre|title=Profiles Theatre|url=http://www.profilestheatre.org/|accessdate=4 April 2012}}</ref>The ''Chicago Tribune'' reviewer wrote:"Interesting and formatively atypical, it strikes me as very much a meditation on what is and is not true, on the ease of rushing to misjudgment, and also a further manifestation of the longstanding authorial fascination with the close link between deep intimacy and dark violence."<ref>Jones, Chris. [http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2012-04-23/entertainment/ct-ent-0424-forest-labute-review-20120423_1_director-joe-jahraus-profiles-theatre-neil-labute "Review. Twists and turns and a few stumbles in LaBute's 'Forest'"] ''Chicago Tribune'', April 23, 2012</ref>
This production was followed by a [[Contemporary American Theater Festival]] ([[Shepherdstown, West Virginia]]) production as part of the 2012 Festival from 6 to 29 July 2012.<ref>{{cite web|last=Contemporary American Theater Festival|title=The Plays|url=http://www.catf.org/2012-season/the-plays|publisher=CATF|accessdate=26 February 2012}}</ref><ref>Treanor, Tim. [http://dctheatrescene.com/2012/07/07/in-a-forest-dark-and-deep-at-catf/ " 'In a Forest, Dark and Deep' at CATF"] dctheatrescene.com, July 7, 2012</ref>
