{{Expand Japanese|JAPAN FM LEAGUE|date=December 2009}}
The {{Nihongo|'''Japan FM League'''|ジャパン エフエム リーグ}} (JFL) is a commercial [[radio network]] in Japan. It is owned by [[J-Wave]] and established in October 1993.
JFL's main ideal is to respect the operation of each of its affiliates, letting each affiliate flourish under its own terms. The network is a [[co-operative]], with each affiliate offering its resources when useful. So for example when J-Wave wants to air a concert or ask for interviews when a group tours in Nagoya, it can easily borrow the studios of [[Zip FM (Aichi)|ZIP-FM]] (the JFL affiliate there) to help produce what's needed.
