{{infobox television | | show_name = Sexcetera | image = Sexcetera logo- 2014-04-25 10-08.jpg | genre = Erotica | starring = Various | runtime = 60 mins | country = [[United States]] | network = [[Playboy TV]] | first_aired = 1998 | last_aired = 2005 |}}
'''''Sexcetera''''' is an [[Television in the United States|American television series]] airing on [[Playboy TV]]. Formatted as a [[News magazine#Broadcast news magazines|newsmagazine]], the program focused on [[human sexuality]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/nypost/access/68449650.html?dids=68449650:68449650&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Oct+20%2C+1998&author=DON+KAPLAN&pub=New+York+Post&desc=OH+BABY!+HERE'S+%22SEX-TY+MINUTES'+%3B+PLAYBOY+LAUNCHES+NEWS+YOU+PROBABLY+WON'T+USE&pqatl=google |title=Archives - New York Post Online Edition |publisher=Pqasb.pqarchiver.com |date=1998-10-20 |accessdate=2013-08-20}}</ref>
''Sexcetera'' is repeated from time to time on [[Real Lives (TV channel)|Real Lives]] and [[Pick (TV channel)|Pick]] in the United Kingdom, RTL 7 in the Netherlands, TV5 in Finland and [[AXN]] in Italy.
Launched in 1998, ''Sexcetera'' ran for more than 80 [[episode]]s. By the time the program went off the air in 2005, it had become one of Playboy TV's longest-running shows.
The show featured four to five [[report]]s per one-hour episode. Filmed throughout the [[United States]] and in [[Europe]], the reports generally covered [[Sexual fetishism|sexual fetishes]], [[adult entertainment]] [[Trade fair|expos]] and gatherings, current [[erotic]] trends, [[sex toy]]s, porn celebrities and tips for couples.
[[Correspondents]] presented their stories in a [[humorous]] style; female correspondents often appeared in the nude. As befitting its subject matter, the series is sexually explicit, with unsimulated sexual activity shown from time to time, with increasing explicitness as the series went on.
