{{Infobox ballet company | name = Spanish National Dance Company | logo = [[File:Spanish National Dance Company (Compañía Nacional de Danza) - logo -01.jpg|150px]] | local_name = ''Compañía Nacional de Danza'' | previous_names = Ballet Nacional de España Clásico | founded = 1979 | venue = Spain {{flagicon|Spain}} | website = [http://cndanza.mcu.es/ cndanza.mcu.es] | artistic_director = José Carlos Martínez<ref>[http://www.elpais.com/articulo/cultura/Jose/Carlos/Martinez/nuevo/director/Compania/Nacional/Danza/elpepucul/20101217elpepucul_3/Tes José Carlos Martínez, nuevo director de la Compañía Nacional de Danza], El País, 17 de diciembre de 2010.</ref> | parent_company = | sister_company = | formation = }} The '''Spanish National Dance Company''', (Compañía Nacional de Danza),<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.sfgate.com/2010-05-01/entertainment/20882938_1_nacho-duato-san-francisco-ballet-troupe |title=Dance review: Compañía Nacional de Danza - SFGate |publisher=Articles.sfgate.com |date=2010-05-01 |accessdate=2010-08-13 | first=Allan | last=Ulrich}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.com/news/2010/may/04/compania-nacional-de-danza-granada/ |title= Compañía Nacional de Danza at the Granada |publisher=The Santa Barbara Independent (Independent.com) |date=2010-05-04 |accessdate=2010-08-13}}</ref> was founded in 1979, originally as under the name of Ballet Nacional de España Clásico. Its first director was dancer [[Victor Ullate]], followed by [[Maria de Avila]], [[Ray Barra]], [[Maya Plisetskaya]], [[Nacho Duato]] (1990-July 2010), Hervé Palito and [[José Carlos Martínez (dancer)|José Carlos Martínez]] since December 2010. [[Image:Raymonda, CND, José Carlos Martínez.jpg|thumb|250px|none|Spanish National Dance Company, 2015]]
In 2018 it was announced that the company would be moving to the [[Railway Museum (Madrid)|railway museum]], near the centre of Madrid.
